Curls that last!
So many of my clients tell me they can’t get their curls to last all day. Using this technique and proper product will ensure long lasting curls everytime! 

I prepped the hair with one of fave products is matrix amplify root lift spray. I spray this product all over my hair. After curling I spray with matrix styling fixer hairspray. This is definitely my fave new hairspray so much hold but not crispy at all.

How I would formula Hailey Biebers brunette hair
This is one of the most requested brunette hair colors that my clients ask for. I use matrix color sync and I would use 5N on the base, 7NGA on the mid lengths and 9NGA on the ends to acheive a similar look.

Perfect blowout combo
Wow this new product from @matrix food for soft is really incredible. It contains Avacado oil and hylauronic acid for softness shine and manageability.  I mixed controller gel with the food for soft oil serum and it’s the perfect amount of hold and softness. I used my revlon styler to do a quick blowout. I only use my revlon on air dryed hair prepped with products to ensure it doesn’t do any damage. If you have done fragile hair make sure you use it on low heat.
#matrixhair
#matrix
#foodforsoft
#bostonhair
#bostonhairstylist
#grwm

Transformation 
My client had some previous breakage from her past that we are working on growing out. Her goal is to have long blonde hair. I full foiled her hair with matrix light master and 20 volume and did some tip outs with light master and 10 volume. I used K18 to protect the hair from anymore breakage. The toner I used is @matrix tonal control in 11PV with a pea of 9V. Matrix tonal control is acidic so it is deposit only and super healthy and shiny. I sewed in a full set of dream catchers weft extensions to give her the length she’s looking for.

Lived in Blonde 
I transitioned Lizzie from traditional foils to more of a “balayage” look. I first did a bunch of lowlights using color sync 8N that I feathered down from the root to about 1/4 to 1/2 way down on the hair strands to extend her natural base down. I next used light master and 20 volume to do a money piece in the front and balayage tips all over. After washing out all the foils I used tonal control 6NGA to base shade and melted that into 11PV. Love the results!!
